WEBVTT

00:05.939 --> 00:07.908
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:07.941 --> 00:10.010
I'LL LEAD IN THE GODMOBILE.
YOU FOLLOW.

00:10.043 --> 00:11.211
ARE WE GONNA SLEEP
IN THAT THING TONIGHT?

00:11.245 --> 00:14.014
TONIGHT AND THE REST
OF OUR LIVES ON THE LAM.

00:14.047 --> 00:15.949
ANY IDEA
WHERE SHE MIGHT BE?

00:15.983 --> 00:18.051
I WANT TO SEE THOSE WASHERS
GOING 24/7.

00:18.085 --> 00:22.489
THIS FAMILY'S GONNA MAKE HASH.
LOTS OF IT.

00:22.523 --> 00:23.857
WON'T THAT BE NICE?

00:23.891 --> 00:24.925
Shane:
I'M IN CHARGE OF AVI.

00:24.958 --> 00:26.793
YOU GUYS
ARE A BAD INFLUENCE.
WHAT?

00:26.827 --> 00:30.197
YOU'RE NOT A BAD INFLUENCE
BECAUSE YOU'RE A DRUG DEALER.
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:30.230 --> 00:32.099
YOU'RE A BAD INFLUENCE BECAUSE
YOU'RE A BAD DRUG DEALER.

00:32.132 --> 00:33.634
I'VE JUST REACHED
MY LIMIT...

00:33.667 --> 00:35.702
OF DEEP OUTLAW SHIT,
SO...

00:35.736 --> 00:36.770
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

00:36.803 --> 00:38.172
I DON'T WANT
TO BE HERE FOREVER.

00:38.205 --> 00:38.805
FINE.

00:38.839 --> 00:40.741
YOU KNOW,
I GOT TO SAY,

00:40.774 --> 00:43.110
I THINK THE HOLY SPIRIT WAS
ACTUALLY MOVING THROUGH ME.

00:43.143 --> 00:44.845
YOU DON'T LISTEN.
YOU NEED SOMEONE TO MAKE YOU?

00:44.878 --> 00:46.880
Nancy: MM‐HMM.

00:46.914 --> 00:48.282
YOU GOT LAID.

00:48.315 --> 00:50.150
I WANT TO STAY HERE
FOR A WHILE.

00:50.184 --> 00:51.718
EHH!

00:51.752 --> 00:54.154
Woman:
PIECE OF SHIT SLUT WHORE!

00:54.188 --> 00:55.789
DID YOU HAVE
A GOOD NIGHT?
OH, SHIT.

00:55.822 --> 00:57.090
YEAH ‐‐ DID YOU
HAVE A GOOD TIME

00:57.124 --> 00:58.859
FUCKING SOMEONE ELSE'S
HUSBAND?!

00:58.892 --> 01:01.528
GOD! OKAY, INSIDE.
INSIDE, INSIDE.

01:02.963 --> 01:04.364
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

01:19.079 --> 01:20.848
Andy: SO, WHAT I'M SAYING
[LAUGHS]

01:20.881 --> 01:22.516
WHAT WE'RE SAYING,
REALLY, IS ‐‐

01:22.549 --> 01:24.718
WE'D GO INSIDE THE DISPENSARY
OURSELVES,

01:24.751 --> 01:26.186
BUT SINCE
YOU'RE THE SUPPLIER...

01:26.220 --> 01:28.388
CUT OUT THE MIDDLE MAN, YES.
OUR OPERATION ‐‐

01:28.422 --> 01:31.925
WE GO FROM STATE TO STATE,
SPREADING OUR MESSAGE,

01:31.959 --> 01:34.895
A SOMETIMES GOOEY
BAKED MESSAGE OF HOPE

01:34.928 --> 01:36.396
TO SICK CHILDREN...

01:36.430 --> 01:38.098
ALL PEOPLE IN NEED.
...GLAUCOMIC PEOPLE,

01:38.131 --> 01:39.600
PEOPLE IN OTHER STATES

01:39.633 --> 01:42.536
LESS PROGRESSIVELY MINDED
THAN COLORADO.

01:42.569 --> 01:43.937
WE JUST WANT YOUR TRIMMINGS,

01:43.971 --> 01:45.873
STUFF YOU'D BE THROWING AWAY
ANYWAY.

01:45.906 --> 01:46.974
WE PAY EXTRA.

01:47.007 --> 01:48.709
WHILE WE'RE SPREADING
THE WORD.

01:48.742 --> 01:50.944
SO, YOU'RE DRUG DEALERS?

01:50.978 --> 01:52.713
PRETTY MUCH.

01:53.947 --> 01:56.783
COOL.

01:56.817 --> 02:01.388
♪♪ TATER TOTS AND WHISKEY SHOTS
AIN'T MUCH OF A MENU... ♪♪

02:01.421 --> 02:03.557
NEBRASKA.

02:03.590 --> 02:07.995
ONLY STATE
WITH A UNICAMERAL LEGISLATURE.

02:08.028 --> 02:09.396
THE BIRTHPLACE
OF KOOL‐AID.

02:09.429 --> 02:11.632
NOT SOMETHING
YOU LEARNED ONLINE.

02:11.665 --> 02:12.900
COME ON!

02:12.933 --> 02:15.969
SIX DAYS!
WHAT DID YOU SEE?

02:16.003 --> 02:18.739
I SAW...
A NUN DRIVING A PICKUP TRUCK.

02:18.772 --> 02:21.475
OKAY, BETTER.
KEEP OBSERVING.

02:21.508 --> 02:26.513
LET THE ROAD BE YOUR SCHOOL.
WATCH, LISTEN.

02:26.547 --> 02:27.848
WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

02:27.881 --> 02:29.683
STEVIE.

02:29.716 --> 02:31.418
OH. GO CHANGE HIM.

02:31.451 --> 02:32.853
I ALWAYS CHANGE HIM.

02:32.886 --> 02:34.788
NO! I...

02:34.821 --> 02:36.156
SOMETIMES DO, DON'T I?

02:36.190 --> 02:38.425
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT SIZE DIAPER HE WEARS?

02:40.861 --> 02:42.062
I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

02:45.265 --> 02:46.967
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR ARM?

02:47.000 --> 02:49.002
I DROPPED MY KEYS
IN THE PORTA‐POTTY,

02:49.036 --> 02:50.204
TIRED TO GET THEM OUT.

02:50.237 --> 02:52.606
THERE WAS A RACCOON
IN THERE.

02:52.639 --> 02:54.741
I PUNCHED HIM OUT.

02:56.710 --> 02:59.546
♪♪ OLD TOWN'S RESTAURANT,
HUNGER VALLEY ♪♪

02:59.580 --> 03:00.747
Nancy: SHANE?

03:00.781 --> 03:02.082
YEAH?

03:02.115 --> 03:05.319
IS THERE SOMETHING YOU WANT
TO TELL ME ABOUT STEVIE'S...

03:05.352 --> 03:06.553
POO?

03:06.587 --> 03:07.921
YOU MEAN THAT GREEN COLOR?

03:07.955 --> 03:09.556
YEAH.

03:09.590 --> 03:11.925
I FIGURED IT WAS NORMAL.
WHY? IS SOMETHING WRONG?

03:11.959 --> 03:14.761
IT'S LIKE RADIOACTIVE

03:14.795 --> 03:19.399
WITH GROSS STRINGY THINGS
IN IT.

03:19.433 --> 03:22.803
DO YOU THINK, UH,
HE ATE SOME HASH?

03:22.836 --> 03:23.804
DID YOU FEED HIM
SOME HASH?

03:23.837 --> 03:26.273
NO! NO.

03:26.306 --> 03:27.374
NO.

03:28.842 --> 03:30.310
SILAS AND SHANE ‐‐

03:30.344 --> 03:33.747
THEY POOPED WEIRD COLORS,
BUT NOT <i>GREEN.</i>

03:33.780 --> 03:36.750
AND NOT AT THIS AGE.

03:36.783 --> 03:38.318
NO,
I WANT A PEDIATRICIAN.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.754
[ SIGHS ]

03:40.787 --> 03:41.855
LIKE LEGITIMATE,
ON THE GRID?

03:41.889 --> 03:43.156
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY.

03:43.190 --> 03:45.659
"IT'S TOO RISKY"
AND "RIDE IT OUT."

03:45.692 --> 03:47.528
I KNOW
ALL THE REASONS WHY.

03:47.561 --> 03:48.896
INSURANCE...

03:48.929 --> 03:51.532
THE FORMS,
OUR SHITTY FAKE I. D. s.

03:51.565 --> 03:52.766
YEAH.

03:52.799 --> 03:53.834
MAYBE I'M OVERREACTING.

03:53.867 --> 03:54.935
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:54.968 --> 03:57.971
OKAY, YOU LOOK AT IT.
YOU TELL ME. GO AHEAD.

04:03.977 --> 04:06.513
OKAY.
WE NEED TO SEE A DOCTOR.

04:06.547 --> 04:08.815
♪♪ ONE PLUS ONE IS TWO,
I KNOW ♪♪

04:08.849 --> 04:10.984
♪♪ THAT IS WHERE YOU START ♪♪

04:11.018 --> 04:13.520
♪♪ I TOOK A SHINY PENNY, PENNY ♪♪

04:13.554 --> 04:16.557
♪♪ PUT IT IN A JAR ♪♪

04:19.960 --> 04:22.563
OKAY, SELL AS MUCH AS YOU CAN.
WE NEED GAS MONEY.

04:22.596 --> 04:25.632
SILAS, YOU'RE IN CHARGE.
SHANE, LISTEN TO YOUR BROTHER.

04:25.666 --> 04:26.867
DOUG, STAY IN YOUR TENT.

04:26.900 --> 04:28.635
10‐4.

04:28.669 --> 04:30.070
SILAS...

04:30.103 --> 04:33.006
REALLY.
YOU'RE IN CHARGE. OKAY?

04:33.040 --> 04:35.209
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

04:36.944 --> 04:39.379
PHISH, DAVE MATTHEWS.

04:39.413 --> 04:40.614
O.A.R.

04:40.647 --> 04:43.550
A WIDESPREAD PANIC TRIBUTE BAND
CALLED RUN SQUIRREL RUN.

04:43.584 --> 04:45.819
MIGHT AS WELL CALL IT "THE
ALL YOU CAN SMOKE FESTIVAL."

04:45.853 --> 04:47.221
YEAH, RIGHT?

04:51.124 --> 04:54.428
HOW THE HELL ARE WE GONNA SELL
HASH AT A KIDS' CONCERT?

04:56.463 --> 04:58.165
ACTUALLY...

04:58.198 --> 04:59.967
THIS MIGHT BE OKAY.

05:00.000 --> 05:03.103
Girl:
MOM! IT'S STARTING!

05:03.136 --> 05:05.539
WE'RE GONNA MISS
THE BUBBLE MACHINE!

05:05.572 --> 05:06.974
JUST ONE SECOND, HONEY.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.909
GIVE ME THAT SHIT.

05:08.942 --> 05:12.079
THANKS.
ENJOY THE CONCERT.

05:12.913 --> 05:14.081
Shane: $25.

05:14.114 --> 05:15.849
I THOUGHT YOU SAID $15.

05:15.883 --> 05:17.351
MAYBE I DID,
MAYBE I DIDN'T.

05:17.384 --> 05:18.719
I'M CONFUSED.

05:18.752 --> 05:20.354
WE'RE DONE HERE.

05:23.223 --> 05:24.525
HEY...

05:28.662 --> 05:30.130
MAYBE I SHOULD SELL,

05:30.163 --> 05:32.900
AND YOU SHOULD SIT
OVER BY THAT TREE.

05:32.933 --> 05:34.101
COME ON.
HE FLAKED.

05:34.134 --> 05:35.903
THAT'S THE THIRD SALE
YOU'VE BALKED.

05:35.936 --> 05:38.372
HAVE A SEAT.
GUARD THE...SAFE.

05:38.405 --> 05:39.673
WHAT?

05:39.706 --> 05:41.642
YOU HEARD MOM.
I'M IN CHARGE.

05:41.675 --> 05:42.976
'CAUSE YOU'RE OLDER.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.312
BECAUSE
I AM MORE RESPONSIBLE

05:45.345 --> 05:48.182
AND HAVE BETTER
INTERPERSONAL SKILLS.

05:48.215 --> 05:49.983
YOU FREAK PEOPLE OUT.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.352
WE DON'T HAVE TO DO
WHATEVER MOM SAYS, YOU KNOW.

05:52.386 --> 05:53.320
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:53.353 --> 05:56.657
OKAY. HOW DO YOU PROPOSE
WE GET GAS MONEY?

05:56.690 --> 05:57.591
I DON'T CARE.

05:57.624 --> 05:59.693
I WANT TO DRINK BEER
AND EAT STADIUM FOOD.

05:59.726 --> 06:01.195
YOU'RE NOT MY BOSS.

06:02.896 --> 06:04.431
YOU'RE RIGHT.

06:04.464 --> 06:05.465
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:05.499 --> 06:08.869
I'M NOT, AND I HAVE
VERY LITTLE DESIRE TO BE,

06:08.902 --> 06:10.904
SO YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:10.938 --> 06:12.239
YOU LEAD.

06:12.272 --> 06:14.074
REALLY?

06:17.544 --> 06:18.679
WHERE TO?

06:18.712 --> 06:20.714
FOLLOW ME.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.695
[ CHILD CRYING ]

06:34.728 --> 06:36.763
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:38.999 --> 06:42.035
SHOULD'VE GONE FOR A SEMITE,
OR AT LEAST AN ASIAN.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.171
WE'RE TAKING
A BIG RISK HERE.

06:44.204 --> 06:48.742
NEVER THOUGHT
I'D FIND MYSELF BACK HERE AGAIN.

06:48.775 --> 06:50.677
AT LEAST
THEY LET YOU PAY CASH.

06:50.711 --> 06:51.979
BORING.
WHAT?

06:52.012 --> 06:53.847
PATIENT'S NAME ‐‐ AVI.

06:53.881 --> 06:55.048
NO.

06:56.884 --> 06:58.085
[ BLOWS ]

07:06.860 --> 07:09.963
"CLOVIS LUDWIG
McKENZIE‐NEWMAN."

07:09.997 --> 07:12.699
GOD, YOU USED TO BE MORE FUN,
YOU KNOW THAT?

07:12.733 --> 07:14.067
MISCHIEVOUS.
LIKE A MINX.

07:14.101 --> 07:15.669
MY CHILD IS SICK.

07:15.702 --> 07:17.971
"MOTHER'S OCCUPATION."
THERE.

07:18.005 --> 07:19.640
You know you want to.

07:22.843 --> 07:24.044
SKYDIVER.

07:24.077 --> 07:25.212
OH. INTERESTING.

07:25.245 --> 07:27.047
I WAS GONNA SAY
"HOMEWRECKER,"

07:27.080 --> 07:29.016
BUT SKYDIVER'S
WAY MORE POSITIVE,

07:29.049 --> 07:30.684
PROBABLY SAFER.

07:30.717 --> 07:34.955
"FATHER'S OCCUPATION" IS, UM,
SCRAPPY DO‐GOODER.

07:34.988 --> 07:36.924
OR HUNKY ALPHA MALE.

07:36.957 --> 07:38.759
ROVING SEX GOD.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.861
DEAD.
WHAT? DEAD?

07:40.894 --> 07:42.829
THAT'S EASIER ‐‐ DEAD.

07:42.863 --> 07:44.932
E‐EASIER THAN WHAT?
SAYING I'M ALIVE?

07:44.965 --> 07:46.500
WHO SAID
ANYTHING ABOUT YOU?

07:46.533 --> 07:48.802
I'M THE DAD.
WE'VE CLEARLY ESTABLISHED THAT.

07:48.836 --> 07:50.904
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH, SURE, FOR NOW.

07:50.938 --> 07:52.206
EXCUSE ME?

07:52.239 --> 07:53.807
FOR NOW.
YOU'RE TOTALLY THE DAD.

07:53.841 --> 07:55.008
DADDY ANDY, NOT DEAD.
SEE? LOOK.

07:55.042 --> 07:57.277
I'M WRITING
"RANDY NEWMAN...

07:57.311 --> 07:58.745
DAD."

07:58.779 --> 08:00.314
UM...UH...

08:00.347 --> 08:01.648
DIPLOMAT.

08:01.682 --> 08:04.251
CULTURAL ATTACHé.

08:04.284 --> 08:05.185
SO WAIT.

08:05.219 --> 08:06.453
ARE YOU ‐‐
JUST SO WE'RE CLEAR ‐‐

08:06.486 --> 08:09.590
ARE YOU SAYING...
I'M HERE ON A TEMPORARY BASIS?

08:09.623 --> 08:10.691
THAT YOU'RE ‐‐ WHAT?

08:10.724 --> 08:13.727
PLANNING SOME OTHER
IMAGINARY FUTURE WITHOUT ME?

08:14.928 --> 08:17.130
YOU SAID BE CREATIVE.

08:22.135 --> 08:23.504
Girl: ARE YOU READY TO BOUNCE,

08:23.537 --> 08:25.839
BOOGIE, SHAKE IT,
AND DO THE TWIST?

08:25.873 --> 08:28.509
COME ON,
LET'S GET UP AND DANCE.

08:28.542 --> 08:29.943
[ ZIPPER UNZIPS ]

08:29.977 --> 08:31.311
♪♪ BOUNCE, BOUNCE, BOUNCE ♪♪

08:31.345 --> 08:32.946
♪♪ BOUNCE, BOUNCE, BOUNCE,
BOUNCE AROUND ♪♪

08:32.980 --> 08:35.382
[ GRUNTS ]

08:35.415 --> 08:38.151
HER NAME IS MEDUSA.

08:38.185 --> 08:41.555
♪♪ BOOGIE, BOOGIE, BOOGIE,
BOOGIE ON DOWN ♪♪

08:42.823 --> 08:44.091
Andy: UH, SO...

08:44.124 --> 08:46.627
WE'RE GONNA TELL STEVIE WHAT ‐‐
THAT I'M HIS UNCLE?

08:46.660 --> 08:48.629
I DON'T KNOW.
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT
WHEN WE GET THERE.

08:48.662 --> 08:51.665
HMM. AND IN THIS
YET‐TO‐BE‐DETERMINED "THERE,"

08:51.698 --> 08:55.969
DO YOU PICTURE ME HAVING
A WIFE/DANISH LOVER, FEMKE,

08:56.003 --> 08:57.271
LIVING WITH US

08:57.304 --> 08:59.506
IN ONE OF THOSE POLYAMOROUS
FREE‐LOVE SITUATIONS?

08:59.540 --> 09:02.142
OR ARE WE GONNA DO MORE OF
A JOINT‐CUSTODY SORT OF THING?

09:02.176 --> 09:03.644
YOU TAKE WEEKDAYS,

09:03.677 --> 09:06.580
I TAKE THE SABBATH
AND ALL MAJOR U. S. HOLIDAYS.

09:06.613 --> 09:09.683
IT'S ALL TOTALLY POSSIBLE,
EXCEPT FOR THE POLYGAMY THING.
POLYAMORY.

09:09.716 --> 09:12.219
'CAUSE I'M JUST ‐‐ I'M CONFUSED
ABOUT THE RULES HERE.

09:12.252 --> 09:13.887
THERE AREN'T ANY RULES.
MM.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.422
BUT THERE ARE.

09:15.455 --> 09:17.858
'CAUSE, CLEARLY, YOU'RE ALLOWED
TO FUCK PEOPLE.

09:17.891 --> 09:19.426
MARRIED BARTENDERS.

09:19.459 --> 09:20.527
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:20.561 --> 09:21.962
BUT ME, NO, GOD FORBID.

09:21.995 --> 09:23.931
YOU CAN...
WHOEVER YOU WANT.

09:23.964 --> 09:25.699
BE MY GUEST.
...AWAY.

09:25.732 --> 09:27.968
OKAY, I WILL.
WORKING ON IT.

09:28.001 --> 09:29.636
GOOD.
YEAH.
SEE THAT NURSE OVER THERE?

09:29.670 --> 09:31.672
DONE.

09:32.573 --> 09:33.574
FEMKE.

09:33.607 --> 09:34.775
WHAT?

09:34.808 --> 09:37.177
DANISH LOVER.

09:37.211 --> 09:38.111
YEAH.

09:38.145 --> 09:39.580
'CAUSE THE WOMEN IN DENMARK
ARE DANISH.

09:39.613 --> 09:40.814
AND THE MEN, TOO.

09:40.848 --> 09:42.816
AND I'M GONNA LIVE
IN DENMARK SOME DAY,

09:42.850 --> 09:44.885
AS LONG AS I'M NOT
IN SOME AMERICAN JAIL

09:44.918 --> 09:46.220
FOR AIDING AND ABETTING.

09:46.253 --> 09:47.988
[ Chuckling ] SINCE WHEN
DO YOU PLAN TO LOVE IN DENMARK?

09:48.021 --> 09:50.157
SINCE FOREVER.

09:50.190 --> 09:52.092
THAT'S MY MOSCOW.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.429
MY SHANGRI‐LA,
MY PITTSBURGH,

09:55.462 --> 09:56.430
MY CANDY MOUNTAIN.

09:56.463 --> 09:58.832
HAVE YOU NEVER READ
ANY RUSSIAN LITERATURE,

09:58.866 --> 10:00.033
YOU UNEDUCATED WOMAN?

10:00.067 --> 10:01.535
[ Sarcastically ]
DANCE MAJOR.

10:01.568 --> 10:04.404
SHUT UP.
I'VE READ STUFF.

10:06.306 --> 10:10.644
I FIGURE
5, 10 YEARS, TOPS, LEFT

10:10.677 --> 10:12.112
BEFORE I START
MY REAL LIFE.

10:12.145 --> 10:16.583
UNLESS, I GUESS,
I'M RAISING STEVIE.

10:16.617 --> 10:18.352
AM I?

10:18.385 --> 10:20.053
RAISING STEVIE?
I DON'T KNOW.

10:24.291 --> 10:26.360
OH. SO...

10:26.393 --> 10:27.661
I TOLD YOU
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

10:27.694 --> 10:29.429
WHEN?
WHEN WE NEED TO.

10:29.463 --> 10:30.497
AHA.

10:30.531 --> 10:32.666
YOU MEAN WHENEVER YOU'VE FOUND
HUSBAND NUMBER FOUR

10:32.699 --> 10:34.868
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN
I'M BACK OUT IN THE COLD.

10:34.902 --> 10:36.103
I NEVER ‐‐

10:36.136 --> 10:38.405
I'M NOT A SUBSTITUTE TEACHER,
NANCE.

10:38.438 --> 10:39.373
I'M INVESTED.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.341
I NEED TO BE A PART
OF THIS CONVERSATION.

10:41.375 --> 10:44.044
ANDY...
'CAUSE I'M ALREADY A PART
OF THIS KID'S LIFE.

10:45.946 --> 10:48.115
Grab Stevie.

10:48.148 --> 10:50.617
We can get to the door
in less than 10 seconds.

10:50.651 --> 10:52.586
NATHALIE NEWMAN.

10:53.921 --> 10:55.923
NATHALIE NEWMAN?

10:55.956 --> 10:58.058
HERE.

10:59.693 --> 11:01.995
OH.

11:11.138 --> 11:14.675
Man: ♪♪ BA‐BA‐BA‐BA‐BANANA,
KI‐KI‐KI‐KIWI ♪♪

11:14.708 --> 11:16.877
SO YOU'RE
A ZOOBIE WOOBIE.

11:16.910 --> 11:18.412
UNDERSTUDY.

11:18.445 --> 11:21.448
YEAH, THE LEAD SINGER'S TAKING
A "PERSONAL WEEK."

11:21.481 --> 11:22.850
Hepatitis.

11:22.883 --> 11:25.452
[ INDISTINCT SINGING
IN DISTANCE ]

11:25.485 --> 11:28.255
THIS OPENING BAND
SUCKS BA‐BA‐BA‐BALLS.

11:28.288 --> 11:29.156
[ COUGHS ]

11:29.189 --> 11:30.924
TELL ME ABOUT IT, RIGHT?

11:30.958 --> 11:33.660
I MEAN,
A SONG ABOUT FRUIT SALAD?

11:33.694 --> 11:35.996
"F" THAT STUFF SIDEWAYS.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.431
BECAUSE "EAT A PAPAYA"

11:37.464 --> 11:40.934
DOES NOT RHYME
WITH "JOIN THE CHOIR."

11:40.968 --> 11:42.836
OKAY?
IT DOESN'T.

11:42.870 --> 11:44.872
RHYME BUTCHERS.

11:44.905 --> 11:46.006
[ COUGHS ]

11:46.039 --> 11:48.275
WHAT DO YOU GUYS
SING ABOUT?
ANIMALS.

11:48.308 --> 11:49.676
MORALITY.

11:49.710 --> 11:51.445
NICE.
THANKS.

11:51.478 --> 11:53.847
MY GRANDPOP USED TO SING SONGS
ABOUT THIS LAMB

11:53.881 --> 11:55.682
WHO OFFED HIS DAD
AND SHTUPPED HIS MOM.

11:55.716 --> 11:56.750
MM.

11:56.783 --> 11:58.151
AND IN THE END,

11:58.185 --> 12:01.188
THE LAMB THROWS HIMSELF FROM
AN OVERPASS TO ESCAPE HIS SINS.

12:02.322 --> 12:05.359
KIND OF LIKE
MY GRANDPOP.

12:05.392 --> 12:06.827
[ EXHALES ]

12:06.860 --> 12:08.729
YEAH, YOU SEE, THAT ‐‐

12:08.762 --> 12:10.964
THAT IS WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

12:10.998 --> 12:12.766
HUH? OOH!

12:12.799 --> 12:14.268
TINY PRETZEL?

12:14.301 --> 12:15.702
OOH.

12:18.372 --> 12:21.041
I LIKE TO LICK THE SALT
OFF A PRETZEL.

12:21.074 --> 12:23.043
THEN I PUT THEM BACK
IN THE BAG...
IN THE BAG?

12:23.076 --> 12:24.111
...AND PEOPLE EAT THEM.

12:24.144 --> 12:25.746
THEY DON'T KNOW
I LICKED THE SALT OFF.

12:25.779 --> 12:28.448
PEOPLE ARE STUPID.
[ LAUGHS ]

12:28.482 --> 12:30.751
WHAT THE FUCK, ANDY?

12:30.784 --> 12:33.420
UH, YEAH, IT'S ALL GOOD
OUT HERE. JOVIAL ATMOSPHERE.

12:33.453 --> 12:36.190
I'VE MADE THREE FRIENDS,
ALL BITTEN BY THE SAME SPIDER.

12:36.223 --> 12:39.526
THEY'RE CONVINCED THEY'RE
GONNA TURN INTO SUPERHEROES.

12:39.560 --> 12:41.261
I HAVEN'T HAD THE HEART
TO TELL THEM ABOUT SEPSIS.

12:41.295 --> 12:43.497
It was a small picture,
right?

12:43.530 --> 12:46.166
WHAT KIND OF BULLSHIT STATION
IS THAT, ANYWAY?

12:47.601 --> 12:48.836
HEY,
DO YOU LIKE CARTOONS?

12:48.869 --> 12:50.637
YEAH.

12:50.671 --> 12:53.507
What?
NOTHING. IT'S FINE.
EVERYTHING'S UNDER CONTROL.

12:58.078 --> 13:01.782
HOW'S, UM,
GIRAFFE DOCTOR?

13:01.815 --> 13:03.584
LARSON? OH,
WE'VE ONLY SEEN THE NURSE.

13:03.617 --> 13:05.886
I HATE DOCTORS' OFFICES.
THIS WAS STUPID.

13:05.919 --> 13:07.487
THIS WAS A BAD IDEA.

13:07.521 --> 13:08.722
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:11.091 --> 13:15.162
OKAY, CLOVIS.
LET'S SEE THAT TUSH.

13:16.697 --> 13:18.332
Man:
I CAN SELL YOU BEER,

13:18.365 --> 13:20.968
BUT YOU CAN'T DRINK IT
INSIDE THE STADIUM.

13:21.001 --> 13:24.071
SILAS, YOU WANT PEANUTS?
I'M BUYING.

13:24.104 --> 13:26.139
SURE.
PEANUTS, PLEASE.

13:26.173 --> 13:27.674
THAT'LL BE $20 EVEN.

13:27.708 --> 13:28.809
RIP‐OFF.

13:28.842 --> 13:31.879
JUST PAY THE GUY.

13:31.912 --> 13:34.681
FUCK.
WHAT?

13:34.715 --> 13:35.983
IT'S NOT HERE.

13:36.016 --> 13:38.218
WHAT'S NOT HERE?
THE MONEY.

13:38.252 --> 13:39.953
SHANE, YOU SAID
YOU PUT IT IN THERE.

13:39.987 --> 13:41.121
IT'S GONE.

13:41.154 --> 13:43.624
ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING?
I GAVE IT TO YOU.

13:43.657 --> 13:44.925
DID YOU ZIP
YOUR BAG SHUT?

13:44.958 --> 13:46.660
I THINK SO.

13:46.693 --> 13:47.961
STOP EATING
THE POPCORN!

13:47.995 --> 13:50.597
GUYS, WE GOT A LINE.

13:50.631 --> 13:53.500
I'M REALLY SORRY,
BUT ‐‐

13:53.534 --> 13:54.635
LOOK, LITTLE DUDE.

13:54.668 --> 13:56.003
PAY FOR THE POPCORN,

13:56.036 --> 13:58.572
OR I WILL BLOW
THIS RAPE WHISTLE...

13:58.605 --> 14:00.607
AND THEN PUNCH YOU.

14:00.641 --> 14:01.708
HERE.

14:04.044 --> 14:05.579
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR PATRONAGE.

14:05.612 --> 14:07.014
YOU OWE ME 20 BUCKS.

14:07.047 --> 14:09.082
YOU OWE MOM $400.

14:13.453 --> 14:15.622
[ COOING ]

14:15.656 --> 14:19.860
SO, RED, WHITE ‐‐
THOSE ARE YOUR DANGER COLORS.

14:19.893 --> 14:21.595
GREEN, LESS SO.

14:21.628 --> 14:24.431
SO GOOD
TO HEAR RIGHT NOW.

14:24.464 --> 14:26.867
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

14:26.900 --> 14:28.268
THAT SAID,
I'M LOOKING AT HIS CHART,

14:28.302 --> 14:29.636
AND I'M CONCERNED
ABOUT HIS WEIGHT.

14:29.670 --> 14:33.774
UH, HE WAS ONLY 6 POUNDS,
2 OUNCES AT BIRTH, SO...

14:33.807 --> 14:35.042
YEAH,
BUT YOU WROTE HERE,

14:35.075 --> 14:38.145
HE'S BEEN GOING TO BED
BETWEEN 7:00 AND 10:00?

14:38.178 --> 14:39.546
UH, IT FLUCTUATES.

14:39.580 --> 14:41.582
WE'VE BEEN TRAVELING
AND SEEING THE COUNTRY.

14:41.615 --> 14:43.116
HUH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:43.150 --> 14:45.786
YOU KNOW,
I‐I SKYDIVE MYSELF,

14:45.819 --> 14:47.688
ONCE A YEAR
ON MY BIRTHDAY.

14:47.721 --> 14:49.656
YEAH.
OH. GOOD FOR YOU.

14:49.690 --> 14:51.391
YEAH, WELL...

14:51.425 --> 14:53.727
SO, YOU'RE NOT
BREAST‐FEEDING?

14:53.760 --> 14:56.496
MM...FORMULA.

14:56.530 --> 14:58.198
AND WHAT ABOUT HIS MOOD?

15:00.968 --> 15:02.669
NORMAL.

15:02.703 --> 15:04.304
HE'S GENERALLY ALERT,

15:04.338 --> 15:06.740
RESPONDING TO YOUR FACE,
SMILING?

15:10.878 --> 15:14.648
UH, HE ‐‐ HE SMILES.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

15:14.681 --> 15:18.252
WELL, WE'RE GONNA CATCH HIM UP
ON HIS VACCINES,

15:18.285 --> 15:21.154
AND I'M GONNA PRESCRIBE
A HIGH‐CALORIC FORMULA.

15:21.188 --> 15:24.725
IT'S THE SAME AS REGULAR
FORMULA ‐‐ MIX IT WITH WATER.

15:24.758 --> 15:28.929
[ Echoing ] AND I RECOMMEND
STICKING TO VERY REGULAR HOURS

15:28.962 --> 15:31.999
WHEN IT COMES TO BEDTIME
AND FEEDING.

15:32.032 --> 15:34.835
YOU KNOW, IT'S ESSENTIAL
FOR INFANTS ‐‐ REGULARITY,

15:34.868 --> 15:36.403
KEEPING THE SAME ROUTINE.

15:36.436 --> 15:39.206
THE KEY
IS ELIMINATING ANYTHING

15:39.239 --> 15:42.609
THAT CAN BE STRESSFUL
FOR THE BABY RIGHT NOW ‐‐

15:42.643 --> 15:45.612
LOUD NOISES
OR INSTABILITY

15:45.646 --> 15:48.248
OR DOMESTIC ISSUES.

15:48.282 --> 15:52.019
BABIES CAN SENSE
THESE THINGS.

15:52.052 --> 15:56.723
AND, OF COURSE, THERE'S
THE LARGER LIFESTYLE CHOICES.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.997
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHAT'D HE SAY?

16:04.031 --> 16:06.934
NOTHING.
STUPID OLD‐MAN DOCTOR.

16:06.967 --> 16:09.870
Boy: IT'S YOU!
IT'S YOU!

16:09.903 --> 16:11.572
IT'S YOU!
IT'S YOU!

16:20.414 --> 16:21.949
KEEP LOOKING.

16:21.982 --> 16:23.917
I CAN'T FIND IT.
IT'S NOT IN HERE.

16:23.951 --> 16:26.353
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
RETRACE OUR STEPS AGAIN.

16:26.386 --> 16:28.188
THERE'S NOWHERE ELSE
TO LOOK.

16:28.222 --> 16:30.090
WE CHECKED
ALL THE TRASH CANS.

16:30.123 --> 16:32.993
SOMEBODY PROBABLY THREW IT AWAY.
IT WAS IN A PLASTIC CUP.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.128
WHICH WAS NOT MY IDEA.

16:36.930 --> 16:38.799
HEY!

16:38.832 --> 16:39.833
SORRY.

16:39.867 --> 16:41.335
GIVE ME MY BEER.

16:42.536 --> 16:44.671
GIVE ME 5 BUCKS.

16:44.705 --> 16:46.807
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:46.840 --> 16:48.275
HOW ABOUT A PANINI?

16:48.308 --> 16:51.712
FIND THE CASH,
YOU GET A BEER.

16:51.745 --> 16:54.314
MAYBE IT'S UNDER
THAT DEAD BIRD.

16:54.348 --> 16:56.316
HOW ABOUT
YOU GIVE ME MY BEER,

16:56.350 --> 16:58.886
AND I DON'T TELL MOM
YOU'RE APPLYING TO COLLEGE?

16:58.919 --> 17:00.888
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:00.921 --> 17:02.589
WE LIVE IN 8 SQUARE FEET
OF SPACE.

17:02.623 --> 17:05.058
YOU'RE READING "HUCK FINN."
WE HAVE NO MORE SECRETS.

17:05.092 --> 17:07.261
DON'T TOUCH MY SHIT.

17:07.294 --> 17:10.130
IT'S COOL.
DO WHAT YOU WANT.

17:11.231 --> 17:14.334
IT'S A CONTINGENCY,
IN CASE MOM DECIDES

17:14.368 --> 17:17.104
TO DRIVE US IN CIRCLES
FOR THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

17:18.639 --> 17:22.042
NOW, WHATEVER. YOU'RE TELLING ME
YOU DON'T HAVE A BACKUP PLAN?

17:22.075 --> 17:25.646
NO.
THE ROAD IS MY SCHOOL NOW.

17:25.679 --> 17:28.115
THIS DUMPSTER'S
MY CLASSROOM.

17:28.148 --> 17:30.884
I'M LEARNING
FROM THIS WASTED PANINI.

17:30.918 --> 17:32.886
OKAY.

17:32.920 --> 17:37.958
YOU FOLLOW YOUR PATH,
I'LL FOLLOW MINE.

17:37.991 --> 17:40.894
COME ON.
WE'RE NEVER GONNA FIND IT.

17:40.928 --> 17:43.630
AND I NEED
ANOTHER BEER.

17:43.664 --> 17:47.401
SOVIET BEAST WE'VE BEEN DRIVING
GETS 4 MILES TO THE GALLON.

17:47.434 --> 17:49.837
MOM'S GONNA KILL ME.

17:49.870 --> 17:54.141
WELL, THEN YOU BETTER
FIND HER SOME GAS.

18:01.849 --> 18:04.751
[ Telephone ringing ]
WOMAN: National Center
for Missing Persons.

18:04.785 --> 18:06.553
How can I help you?

18:06.587 --> 18:07.888
HI.

18:07.921 --> 18:10.424
UH...I'M CALLING IN RESPONSE
TO ONE OF YOUR,

18:10.457 --> 18:11.959
UH, POSTS.

18:11.992 --> 18:14.294
I THINK I ‐‐ I SAW SOMEONE,
MAYBE.

18:14.328 --> 18:16.396
Which case?

18:16.430 --> 18:19.166
BOTWIN? NANCY.

18:19.199 --> 18:22.970
UH...LONG HAIR, BROWNISH.

18:23.003 --> 18:24.671
I FORGET
THE OTHER ONE'S NAME.

18:24.705 --> 18:26.874
IT WAS, UM ‐‐
I‐IT WAS A BABY.

18:26.907 --> 18:28.575
Please hold.

18:30.277 --> 18:31.945
LIPSCHITZ: Federal Bureau
of Investigation.

18:31.979 --> 18:33.447
OH, GOD. UGH.

18:39.653 --> 18:42.756
I THINK THAT WAS HER.

18:47.060 --> 18:49.963
Nancy:
THIS ISN'T WORKING.

18:49.997 --> 18:51.965
I CAN'T RAISE STEVIE
IN THE BACK OF AN RV.

18:51.999 --> 18:53.300
Andy: YEAH, I AGREE.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.837
I LOVE THE ROAD.
NO PLACE FOR A BABY.

18:56.870 --> 18:59.940
IT'S NOT LIKE
I CAN JUST...

18:59.973 --> 19:02.543
SETTLE DOWN
AND PLAY HOUSE SOMEWHERE,

19:02.576 --> 19:06.647
BECAUSE ‐‐ OOPS ‐‐ I'VE
GOT A FUCKING AMBER ALERT
OUT ON ME.

19:06.680 --> 19:09.283
[ Laughing ] RIGHT?
W‐WHERE DID THAT COME FROM?

19:09.316 --> 19:11.985
THAT SAID, I‐I THOUGHT
THE PICTURE WAS GOOD.

19:12.019 --> 19:13.720
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:13.754 --> 19:15.856
I‐I DON'T HAVE
ANY MORE OPTIONS.

19:15.889 --> 19:19.126
EVERYBODY UP MY ASS.

19:19.159 --> 19:21.528
NOW I GOT
THIS FUCKING DOCTOR

19:21.562 --> 19:24.498
TELLING ME STEVIE NEEDS
CHECK‐UPS AND SHOTS.

19:24.531 --> 19:27.768
AND I JUST ‐‐ I'M SO DONE
WITH THIS COUNTRY.

19:27.801 --> 19:31.505
WE NEED TO GO
FAR, FAR AWAY.

19:31.538 --> 19:34.174
COPENHAGEN.

19:34.208 --> 19:36.510
COMPLETE OPPOSITE
OF AMERICA.

19:36.543 --> 19:38.879
YEAH. COPENHAGEN.

19:38.912 --> 19:41.148
CAPRI.
CAPRI SOUNDS NICE.

19:41.181 --> 19:44.418
OKAY. LOOK, I'M GOING TO
COPENHAGEN WITH OR WITHOUT YOU.

19:44.451 --> 19:46.653
SO EITHER YOU CAN
HITCH YOUR WAGON

19:46.687 --> 19:48.055
TO THE ANDY‐AND‐FEMKE
TRAIN,

19:48.088 --> 19:52.259
OR, UH, YOU CAN RAISE
STEVIE ALONE, ON THE RUN.

19:52.292 --> 19:56.730
IS THAT SOME KIND
OF ULTIMATUM?

19:56.763 --> 19:59.132
HEAR ME OUT.
NORDIC PEOPLE.

19:59.166 --> 20:01.969
VERY PEACEFUL.
EXTREMELY LOW CRIME RATE.

20:02.002 --> 20:03.971
HIGH QUALITY OF LIFE.

20:04.004 --> 20:05.839
UNIVERSAL HEALTHCARE.

20:05.873 --> 20:08.842
OPEN‐FACED SANDWICHES.

20:08.876 --> 20:10.944
BIKES EVERYWHERE!

20:10.978 --> 20:12.746
I'VE DONE
GOOGLE STREET VIEW.

20:12.779 --> 20:14.815
IT'S LIKE
SANTA'S VILLAGE.

20:14.848 --> 20:17.451
I EVEN GOT A NEIGHBORHOOD
PICKED OUT.

20:17.484 --> 20:19.052
I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO PRONOUNCE IT.

20:19.086 --> 20:20.387
IT STARTS WITH AN "R."

20:20.420 --> 20:23.724
THEIR CORE VALUE ‐‐
GET THIS ‐‐

20:23.757 --> 20:25.158
HYGGE.

20:25.192 --> 20:27.461
IT MEANS "COZINESS"...

20:27.494 --> 20:33.100
AS IN RELAXED, SEDATE,
STRESS‐FREE.

20:34.968 --> 20:36.637
COPENHAGEN.

20:38.539 --> 20:41.041
COPENHAGEN.

20:41.074 --> 20:44.478
WE'RE GONNA NEED
PASSPORTS.

20:45.946 --> 20:47.047
OKAY. YEAH.

20:47.080 --> 20:50.450
IT...COULD BE TOUGH,
BUT OKAY.

20:52.019 --> 20:53.220
LOTS OF MONEY.

20:53.253 --> 20:55.556
WELL, WE'LL SELL
LOTS OF DRUGS.

20:55.589 --> 20:57.224
NO. NO.

20:57.257 --> 21:00.561
ONE BIG SELL,
AND IT'S...DONE.

21:00.594 --> 21:01.562
PFFT!

21:01.595 --> 21:02.996
WOW. OKAY.

21:03.030 --> 21:05.899
UM...YOU SERIOUS?

21:05.933 --> 21:06.934
MOSCOW.

21:06.967 --> 21:08.735
ELSA...

21:08.769 --> 21:11.071
FEMKE.
WHATEVER.

21:13.173 --> 21:15.542
IT'S A WONDERFUL
WONDERFUL.

21:15.576 --> 21:16.877
WHAT?

21:16.910 --> 21:20.614
YOU ONCE SAID THAT
TO ME.

21:20.647 --> 21:22.216
I DID?

21:22.249 --> 21:24.518
YEAH.

21:24.551 --> 21:26.019
[ MAN COUGHING ]

21:26.053 --> 21:29.323
[ WOMAN SINGING INDISTINCTLY ]

21:38.131 --> 21:41.935
TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOUR ACTIONS.

21:41.969 --> 21:43.737
BE A HERO.

21:43.770 --> 21:46.173
Yeah.

21:51.078 --> 21:54.414
[ GAGS ] I CAN'T.
I‐I CAN'T. THE FUMES.

21:54.448 --> 21:55.449
I'M GONNA BE SICK.

21:55.482 --> 21:59.052
THE WHOLE FAMILY
IS DEPENDING ON YOU.

22:00.721 --> 22:02.856
Do it.

22:02.890 --> 22:04.458
Do it.

22:04.491 --> 22:08.195
DO IT. DO IT. DO IT.

22:08.228 --> 22:11.665
DO IT! DO IT! DO IT!

22:11.698 --> 22:13.133
DO IT.

22:13.166 --> 22:15.802
GRAB THE CAR'S NUT SACK.

22:15.836 --> 22:18.672
[ GURGLING ]

22:18.705 --> 22:21.909
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:21.942 --> 22:23.810
I'M A HERO!

22:23.844 --> 22:25.512
I'M A HERO!

22:25.546 --> 22:27.080
YES!

22:27.114 --> 22:29.416
[ Laughing ] YES.

22:29.449 --> 22:31.051
HM.

22:31.084 --> 22:33.587
I CAN'T TASTE MY BEER
ANYMORE.

22:35.923 --> 22:38.292
YOU DID GOOD.

22:38.325 --> 22:40.160
THANKS.

22:45.933 --> 22:47.634
THANKS FOR THE BLOWJOB.

22:47.668 --> 22:50.604
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.
GO LIKE THIS. [ EXHALES ]

22:50.637 --> 22:51.471
[ EXHALES ]

22:51.505 --> 22:53.607
OH, NICE.
SOMEBODY HAD A GOOD TIME.

22:53.640 --> 22:55.475
I'LL DEAL WITH THAT
LATER.

22:55.509 --> 22:57.177
UH, I LOST THE ‐‐

22:57.211 --> 22:59.246
$400, GIVE OR TAKE.

22:59.279 --> 23:01.815
NICE WORK.
NICE WORK, SILAS.

23:01.849 --> 23:05.085
MUST'VE FALLEN OUT OF YOUR BAG
WHEN YOU LEFT IT UNZIPPED

23:05.118 --> 23:06.854
SO ANYONE COULD REACH IN
AND TAKE IT.

23:06.887 --> 23:08.455
UH‐HUH.

23:08.488 --> 23:09.623
ASSHOLE.

23:09.656 --> 23:11.725
[ DOUG CLEARS THROAT ]

23:21.635 --> 23:23.403
SO, WHAT'S NEXT?

23:23.437 --> 23:26.940
ANOTHER CONCERT?

23:26.974 --> 23:30.043
PIONEER CITY PART TWO?

23:31.745 --> 23:33.447
MOM?

23:33.480 --> 23:35.415
[ STEVIE COOING ]

23:35.449 --> 23:36.817
COPENHAGEN.

23:36.850 --> 23:41.755
BUT...ONE MORE STOP
FIRST.

23:45.125 --> 23:47.861
<i>OH, MY SISTER NANCY.</i>

23:47.895 --> 23:50.597
<i>WHAT A BIG</i>
<i>FUCKING SURPRISE.</i>

23:50.631 --> 23:51.965
[ <i>CHUCKLES</i>]

23:51.999 --> 23:55.269
<i>OH, THIS ‐‐</i>
<i>UM, THESE ARE MINE.</i>

23:55.302 --> 23:59.873
THEY'RE, UM ‐‐ THEY'RE ALL,
<i>LIKE, A WORK IN PROGRESS,</i>

23:59.907 --> 24:02.910
<i>LIKE ME.</i>

24:02.943 --> 24:05.579
<i>I'M DIVORCED.</i>

24:05.612 --> 24:08.182
<i>YOU'RE CUTE.</i>

24:08.215 --> 24:10.851
<i>I'M SORRY.</i>
<i>WHAT WAS THE QUESTION?</i>

24:10.884 --> 24:13.387
<i>OH, MICHIGAN.</i>
<i>RIGHT, RIGHT.</i>

24:13.420 --> 24:14.688
[ <i>SIGHS</i>]

24:14.721 --> 24:16.156
<i>MICHIGAN'S BORING.</i>

24:16.190 --> 24:18.592
<i>TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF.</i>

24:21.261 --> 24:22.796
<i>OKAY.</i>

24:22.829 --> 24:24.698
<i>UM, DAD WORKED FOR FORD,</i>

24:24.731 --> 24:28.035
JUST LIKE EVERYONE ELSE WITHIN
A 30‐MILE RADIUS OF DETROIT.

24:28.068 --> 24:32.072
<i>UH...MOM DRANK A LOT.</i>

24:32.105 --> 24:33.941
<i>UH, THEY'RE BOTH DEAD.</i>

24:33.974 --> 24:35.976
<i>THE HOUSE?</i>

24:36.009 --> 24:38.979
[ <i>Laughing</i>]
<i>IT WAS A TOTAL SHIT BOX.</i>

24:39.012 --> 24:40.180
<i>REALLY.</i>

24:40.214 --> 24:44.518
<i>BUT, UM, I DON'T KNOW.</i>
<i>I LIKED IT.</i>

24:44.551 --> 24:46.887
<i>UH, IT WAS COZY.</i>

24:46.920 --> 24:48.488
<i>UGH.</i>

24:48.522 --> 24:50.457
<i>THERE WAS THIS, UM...</i>

24:50.490 --> 24:55.896
<i>MERMAID MAILBOX</i>
<i>THAT MY DAD MADE.</i>

24:55.929 --> 24:59.166
[ <i>CHUCKLES</i>]

25:01.768 --> 25:04.171
T‐TAKE A RIGHT.
UP HERE. UP HERE.

25:11.712 --> 25:15.883
♪♪ OUT IN THE DARK,
SHAKING HANDS IN THE STREET ♪♪

25:15.916 --> 25:20.020
♪♪ I'M DRIFTING ♪♪

25:20.053 --> 25:26.326
♪♪ DRIFTING AWAY FROM MY FAMILY
TOWARDS MY FOES ♪♪

25:27.828 --> 25:34.401
♪♪ MY MOTHER TOLD ME,
"YOU'LL REAP WHAT YOU SOW" ♪♪

25:36.136 --> 25:42.743
♪♪ WHAT YOU MOST WANT
IS BAD FOR ME, YOU KNOW ♪♪

25:44.611 --> 25:51.118
♪♪ BUT WHEN WE GET SAD,
WE KNOW WHERE TO GO ♪♪

25:52.753 --> 25:58.125
